The paper is about recommendation systems, which typically fall under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of knowledge graphs and attention mechanisms also suggests a focus on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with modeling relations among items, which is a common problem in Database (cs.DB) research.
